<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: SAN DIEGO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 17-year-old boy convicted of first-degree murder was ordered Thursday to 
undergo a diagnostic study at the California Youth Authority before sentencing. 
</P>
<P>
DeShawn Stallsworth, who had been certified by Juvenile Court to be tried as an 
adult, will be sentenced in San Diego Superior Court within 90 days after the 
study is finished. 
</P>
<P>
Stallsworth pleaded guilty to first-degree murder in the Aug. 8 slaying of 
Armando Bracamontes, 16, who was shot in the head in a gang-related incident on 
Wunderlin Avenue in San Diego. 
</P>
<P>
Stallsworth could be sentenced to a maximum of 25 years to life in state 
prison. 
</P>
