<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTH BAY DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: ROUTE 103 CLOSES TONIGHT FOR FILMING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
All northbound and southbound lanes of the Terminal Island Freeway (Route 103) 
between Willow Street in Long Beach and Henry Ford Avenue approaching Terminal 
Island will be closed from 8 p.m. tonight to midnight Sunday to allow a film to 
be shot on the roadway. 
</P>
<P>
In addition, the freeway on- and off-ramps at Anaheim Street and Pacific Coast 
Highway will be closed during the same 28-hour period. 
</P>
