<HEADLINE>
<P>
NORTHRIDGE TRAVELS FRESH OFF A VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JOHN ORTEGA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Cal State Northridge men's basketball team, fresh off a come-from-behind 
victory over Biola on Wednesday, will travel to Cedar City, Utah, for a 
nonconference game with Southern Utah State at 7:30 tonight. 
</P>
<P>
Northridge (4-7), which snapped a three-game losing streak with its 62-54 
decision over Biola, will again be without the services of starting guard 
Eugene Humphrey, who suffered a severely bruised right thigh against Sacramento 
State last Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
"Gene is really hurting right now," Coach Pete Cassidy said. "He's limping 
badly. We're just hoping now to have him back for the start of conference." 
</P>
<P>
Freshman Bill Mazurie will again start in Humphrey's place. 
</P>
<P>
Senior Derrick Gathers, who has led Northridge in both scoring and rebounding 
in six games this season, is averaging a team-high 20.4 points and 8.5 rebounds 
a game. 
</P>
<P>
After playing Division I Southern Utah State tonight, Northridge will return 
home to play Division III Colorado College on Monday. 
</P>
<P>
The Matadors begin California Collegiate Athletic Assn. play at Cal Poly San 
Luis Obispo on Friday, followed by a conference game at Cal State Bakersfield 
on Saturday. JOHN ORTEGA 
</P>
</TEXT>
