<HEADLINE>
<P>
TRANSMITTING AIDS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Dr. Neil Solomon 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Question: Is it possible for one woman to give the virus that causes AIDS to 
another woman while having sex? 
</P>
<P>
Answer: Transmission of the AIDS virus from one woman to another is very rare, 
but it has been reported. Transmission may occur as a result of the exchange of 
blood either during menses or as a result of trauma. 
</P>
<P>
For Thomas, Charlottesville, Va.: Regardless of the temperature, you should not 
work on your car in a garage with the doors closed. Carbon monoxide can do a 
lot more damage than simply causing a headache. 
</P>
</TEXT>
