<HEADLINE>
<P>
CALIFORNIA IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
SACRAMENTO; 
</P>
<P>
FISH AND GAME DEPT. CRITICIZED IN REPORT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
California's Fish and Game officials fail to protect the state's wildlife 
adequately, mismanage their regional offices and cannot deal effectively with 
other state agencies, according to the governmental watchdog agency. The Little 
Hoover Commission, a constitutionally authorized advisory body, said in a 
report to the state Legislature that state wildlife policy is crippled by the 
perception that "the Fish and Game Commission and the Department of Fish and 
Game have isolated themselves from the major groups concerned with the 
preservation of fish, game and habitat, while at the same time frequently 
straining relations with other government agencies, sporting groups and 
developers." 
</P>
</TEXT>
