METRO DIGEST LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: PANEL TO ADVISE REINER ON CHILD SUPPORT ISSUE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Los Angeles County Dist. Atty. Ira Reiner has established a panel to advise him 
on ways to improve child support collections from "delinquent dads," attorney 
Gloria Allred announced Thursday after meeting with Reiner for an hour. 
</P>
<P>
The panel will include Chief Deputy Dist. Atty. Greg Thompson and other members 
of the office along with Allred and members of the Women's Equal Rights Legal 
Defense and Education Fund, an activist group. Allred said Reiner was receptive 
to other ideas she presented, including airing on local cable television 
stations the names and last known addresses of parents who have failed to pay 
child support. 
</P>
<P>
Allred, who was evicted from Reiner's outer office several years ago after he 
refused to discuss the issue with her, said she did not promise to support 
Reiner in his announced bid for state attorney general this year in return for 
establishing the child support panel. 
</P>
