<P>
Cornerback Lewis Billups of the Cincinnati Bengals was arrested on charges of 
carrying a concealed weapon and improperly handling a gun in his car, 
Cincinnati police said. 
</P>
<P>
Police said that two undercover officers saw Billups, 25, display a handgun in 
a vehicle Thursday in downtown Cincinnati. They put out a broadcast for 
Billups' arrest and the defensive back was stopped a few miles away in Ft. 
Wright, Ky., just outside Cincinnati. Billups was released from jail Thursday 
night after posting $500 bond. He was scheduled for arraignment this morning. 
</P>
