<HEADLINE>
<P>
GROVE SHAKESPEARE FESTIVAL ANNOUNCES 'TWELFTH NIGHT' CAST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JAN HERMAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
GARDEN GROVE 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Grove Shakespeare Festival has set the casting for "Twelfth Night, Or As 
You Will," which opens Jan. 19 at the Gem Theatre. The major leads are to be 
John-Frederick Jones as Malvolio; Carl Reggiardo as Orsino; Kerry Noonan as 
Viola, and Alicia Wollerton as Olivia. 
</P>
<P>
Jones previously appeared at the Grove's Festival Amphitheatre in the title 
role of "Julius Caesar" and as Claudius in "Hamlet." He was last seen as Mr. 
Bohun in Shaw's "You Never Can Tell" at South Coast Repertory in Costa Mesa. 
Reggiardo starred at the Gem as Sherlock Holmes in "Sherlock's Last Case" and 
was seen this summer as de Guiche in the Grove's "Cyrano de Bergerac." 
</P>
<P>
Noonan, previously in the Grove's "Two Gentlemen of Verona," has played at SCR 
in "Going for the Gold" and "A Christmas Carol." Wollerton has appeared as 
Luciana in the Grove's "The Comedy of Errors" and as Cordelia in the Grove's 
"King Lear." 
</P>
<P>
Also cast: Steve Henry as Sir Toby Belch, Steve Peterson as Sir Andrew 
Eguecheeke and Gary Bell as Feste. JAN HERMAN 
</P>
</TEXT>
